Core Skill Sets for a DevOps Engineer

1. 🧰 Operating Systems & Scripting
      Proficiency in Linux/Unix (file systems, networking, permissions, process control)
      Strong in Shell scripting (Bash), Python, or Go
2. ☁️ Cloud Platforms
      Deep hands-on experience with at least one:
       AWS (EC2, S3, ECS, EKS, Lambda, CloudWatch, IAM, etc.)
       Azure, Google Cloud, or OCI
       Infrastructure cost management & cloud security are big pluses

3. 📦 Containers & Orchestration
      Docker: Build, run, and manage containers
      Kubernetes (K8s): Deploy and manage microservices at scale
      Understand Helm, kubeadm, Kustomize, etc.
4. 🛠️ CI/CD Pipelines
      Build and maintain pipelines using:
        Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, CircleCI, ArgoCD
      Automate testing, deployment, and rollbacks
5. 💾 Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
      Write reproducible infrastructure using:
        Terraform, CloudFormation, Pulumi
      Know how to version, audit, and manage infrastructure

6. 🔒 Monitoring, Logging & Observability
     Tools like:
        Prometheus + Grafana
        ELK/EFK Stack (Elasticsearch, Fluentd, Kibana)
        Datadog, New Relic, Dynatrace, Splunk
        Set up alerts, dashboards, log aggregation

7. 🔐 Security & Compliance (DevSecOps)
      Secure CI/CD pipelines
      Manage secrets using Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.
      Perform static/dynamic security scans (e.g., Snyk, SonarQube)

8. 🔁 Source Control & GitOps
     Strong Git skills
     Experience with branching strategies, PR workflows
     GitOps tools like FluxCD or ArgoCD are a plus

9.  🧪 Testing & Automation
      Automate everything: unit, integration, smoke tests
      Support test environments and rollbacks

10. 🧑‍🤝‍🧑 Soft Skills
    Collaboration across teams (devs, QA, infra)
    Problem-solving & root cause analysis
    Comfortable with on-call and incident response



